# Lời giải

Ta có $\left(\overrightarrow{AC}, \overrightarrow{CB}\right)=180^{\circ}-\left(\overrightarrow{CA}, \overrightarrow{CB}\right)=180^{\circ}-\widehat{ACB}$.

Mà $\cos \widehat{ACB}=\dfrac{AC}{BC}=\dfrac{1}{2}$ nên $\widehat{ACB}=60^{\circ}$.

Do đó $\left(\overrightarrow{AC}, \overrightarrow{CB}\right)=180^{\circ}-60^{\circ}=120^{\circ}$.

Vậy $\cos (\overrightarrow{AC}, \overrightarrow{CB})=\cos 120^{\circ}=-\dfrac{1}{2}=-0,5$.

